{
  "doc_id": "12271",
  "text": "Shedding of glycocalyx components including PGs and GAGs has been shown in experimental models of vascular barrier disruption, including TNF-␣-induced inflammation [CITATION_1] , hemorrhagic shock (16), endotoxemia [CITATION_2] , and hyperglycemia [CITATION_3] . Moreover, loss of endothelial glycocalyx is associated with clinical conditions following surgery [CITATION_4] , trauma [CITATION_5] , and ischemia reperfusion [CITATION_6] . Therefore, understanding the mechanisms leading to glycocalyx shedding should aid in developing new methods to protect the endothelium from these processes.",
